Under the agreement, the online hospitality service will promote the Mother City abroad. CAPE TOWN - Airbnb has inked a collaboration deal with the City of Cape Town. Under the agreement, the online hospitality service will promote the Mother City abroad. In Cape Town, there are more than 17,000 Airbnb listings. The City's Zara Nicholson said: “As part of the collaboration agreement, Airbnb and the City of Cape Town will join forces to boost the attractiveness of the city and enable Airbnb hosts to become ambassadors of the Mother City. We will work together to bring community-led tourism to townships and support greater economic and social empowerment.”